12// Local handles should be trivially copyable so that the contained value can be
13// efficiently passed by value in a register. This is important for two
14// reasons: better performance and a simpler ABI for generated code and fast
15// API calls.
16ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(api_internal::IndirectHandleBase);
17#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_LOCAL
18ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(api_internal::DirectHandleBase);
19#endif
20ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(LocalBase<Object>);
21
22#if !(defined(V8_ENABLE_LOCAL_OFF_STACK_CHECK) && V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_TRIVIAL_ABI)
23// Direct local handles should be trivially copyable, for the same reasons as
24// above. In debug builds, however, where we want to check that such handles are
25// stack-allocated, we define a non-default copy constructor and destructor.
26// This makes them non-trivially copyable. We only do it in builds where we can
27// declare them as "trivial ABI", which guarantees that they can be efficiently
28// passed by value in a register.
29ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(Local<Object>);
30ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(internal::LocalUnchecked<Object>);
31ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(MaybeLocal<Object>);
32#endif

38ElementsKind GetTypedArrayElementsKind(CTypeInfo::Type type) {
39 switch (type) {
40 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
41 return UINT8_ELEMENTS;
42 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
43 return INT32_ELEMENTS;
44 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
45 return UINT32_ELEMENTS;
46 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
47 return BIGINT64_ELEMENTS;
48 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
49 return BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS;
50 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
51 return FLOAT32_ELEMENTS;
52 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
53 return FLOAT64_ELEMENTS;
54 case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
55 case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
56 case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
57 case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
58 case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
59 case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
60 case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
61 UNREACHABLE();
62 }
63}

65OverloadsResolutionResult ResolveOverloads(
66 const FastApiCallFunctionVector& candidates, unsigned int arg_count) {
67 DCHECK_GT(arg_count, 0);
68
69 static constexpr int kReceiver = 1;
70
71 // Only the case of the overload resolution of two functions, one with a
72 // JSArray param and the other with a typed array param is currently
73 // supported.
74 DCHECK_EQ(candidates.size(), 2);
75
76 for (unsigned int arg_index = kReceiver; arg_index < arg_count; arg_index++) {
77 int index_of_func_with_js_array_arg = -1;
78 int index_of_func_with_typed_array_arg = -1;
79 CTypeInfo::Type element_type = CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid;
80
81 for (size_t i = 0; i < candidates.size(); i++) {
82 const CTypeInfo& type_info =
83 candidates[i].signature->ArgumentInfo(arg_index);
84 CTypeInfo::SequenceType sequence_type = type_info.GetSequenceType();
85
86 if (sequence_type == CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence) {
87 DCHECK_LT(index_of_func_with_js_array_arg, 0);
88 index_of_func_with_js_array_arg = static_cast<int>(i);
89 } else if (sequence_type == CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsTypedArray) {
90 DCHECK_LT(index_of_func_with_typed_array_arg, 0);
91 index_of_func_with_typed_array_arg = static_cast<int>(i);
92 element_type = type_info.GetType();
93 } else {
94 DCHECK_LT(index_of_func_with_js_array_arg, 0);
95 DCHECK_LT(index_of_func_with_typed_array_arg, 0);
96 }
97 }
98
99 if (index_of_func_with_js_array_arg >= 0 &&
100 index_of_func_with_typed_array_arg >= 0) {
101 return {static_cast<int>(arg_index), element_type};
102 }
103 }
104
105 // No overload found with a JSArray and a typed array as i-th argument.
106 return OverloadsResolutionResult::Invalid();
107}

109bool CanOptimizeFastSignature(const CFunctionInfo* c_signature) {
110 USE(c_signature);
111
112#if defined(V8_OS_MACOS) && defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64)
113 // On MacArm64 hardware we don't support passing of arguments on the stack.
114 if (c_signature->ArgumentCount() > 8) {
115 return false;
116 }
117#endif // defined(V8_OS_MACOS) && defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64)
118
119#ifndef V8_ENABLE_FP_PARAMS_IN_C_LINKAGE
120 if (c_signature->ReturnInfo().GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32 ||
121 c_signature->ReturnInfo().GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64) {
122 return false;
123 }
124#endif
125
126#ifndef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
127 if (c_signature->ReturnInfo().GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64 ||
128 c_signature->ReturnInfo().GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64) {
129 return false;
130 }
131#endif
132
133 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < c_signature->ArgumentCount(); ++i) {
134 USE(i);
135
136#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
137 // Clamp lowering in EffectControlLinearizer uses rounding.
138 uint8_t flags = uint8_t(c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i).GetFlags());
139 if (flags & uint8_t(CTypeInfo::Flags::kClampBit)) {
140 return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_2);
141 }
142#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
143
144#ifndef V8_ENABLE_FP_PARAMS_IN_C_LINKAGE
145 if (c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i).GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32 ||
146 c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i).GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64) {
147 return false;
148 }
149#endif
150
151#ifndef V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
152 if (c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i).GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64 ||
153 c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i).GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64) {
154 return false;
155 }
156#endif
157 }
158
159 return true;
160}

164class FastApiCallBuilder {
165 public:
166 FastApiCallBuilder(Isolate* isolate, Graph* graph,
167 GraphAssembler* graph_assembler,
168 const GetParameter& get_parameter,
169 const ConvertReturnValue& convert_return_value,
170 const InitializeOptions& initialize_options,
171 const GenerateSlowApiCall& generate_slow_api_call)
172 : isolate_(isolate),
173 graph_(graph),
174 graph_assembler_(graph_assembler),
175 get_parameter_(get_parameter),
176 convert_return_value_(convert_return_value),
177 initialize_options_(initialize_options),
178 generate_slow_api_call_(generate_slow_api_call) {}
179
180 Node* Build(const FastApiCallFunctionVector& c_functions,
181 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature, Node* data_argument);
182
183 private:
184 Node* WrapFastCall(const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, int inputs_size,
185 Node** inputs, Node* target,
186 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature, int c_arg_count,
187 Node* stack_slot);
188
189 Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }
190 Graph* graph() const { return graph_; }
191 GraphAssembler* gasm() const { return graph_assembler_; }
192 Isolate* isolate_;
193 Graph* graph_;
194 GraphAssembler* graph_assembler_;
195 const GetParameter& get_parameter_;
196 const ConvertReturnValue& convert_return_value_;
197 const InitializeOptions& initialize_options_;
198 const GenerateSlowApiCall& generate_slow_api_call_;
199};

201Node* FastApiCallBuilder::WrapFastCall(const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
202 int inputs_size, Node** inputs,
203 Node* target,
204 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature,
205 int c_arg_count, Node* stack_slot) {
206 // CPU profiler support
207 Node* target_address = __ ExternalConstant(
208 ExternalReference::fast_api_call_target_address(isolate()));
209 __ Store(StoreRepresentation(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
210 kNoWriteBarrier),
211 target_address, 0, __ BitcastTaggedToWord(target));
212
213 // Update effect and control
214 if (stack_slot != nullptr) {
215 inputs[c_arg_count + 1] = stack_slot;
216 inputs[c_arg_count + 2] = __ effect();
217 inputs[c_arg_count + 3] = __ control();
218 } else {
219 inputs[c_arg_count + 1] = __ effect();
220 inputs[c_arg_count + 2] = __ control();
221 }
222
223 // Create the fast call
224 Node* call = __ Call(call_descriptor, inputs_size, inputs);
225
226 // Reset the CPU profiler target address.
227 __ Store(StoreRepresentation(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
228 kNoWriteBarrier),
229 target_address, 0, __ IntPtrConstant(0));
230
231 return call;
232}

234Node* FastApiCallBuilder::Build(const FastApiCallFunctionVector& c_functions,
235 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature,
236 Node* data_argument) {
237 const int c_arg_count = c_signature->ArgumentCount();
238
239 // Hint to fast path.
240 auto if_success = __ MakeLabel();
241 auto if_error = __ MakeDeferredLabel();
242
243 // Overload resolution
244 bool generate_fast_call = false;
245 OverloadsResolutionResult overloads_resolution_result =
246 OverloadsResolutionResult::Invalid();
247
248 if (c_functions.size() == 1) {
249 generate_fast_call = true;
250 } else {
251 DCHECK_EQ(c_functions.size(), 2);
252 overloads_resolution_result = ResolveOverloads(c_functions, c_arg_count);
253 if (overloads_resolution_result.is_valid()) {
254 generate_fast_call = true;
255 }
256 }
257
258 if (!generate_fast_call) {
259 // Only generate the slow call.
260 return generate_slow_api_call_();
261 }
262
263 // Generate fast call.
264
265 const int kFastTargetAddressInputIndex = 0;
266 const int kFastTargetAddressInputCount = 1;
267
268 int extra_input_count = FastApiCallNode::kEffectAndControlInputCount +
269 (c_signature->HasOptions() ? 1 : 0);
270
271 Node** const inputs = graph()->zone()->AllocateArray<Node*>(
272 kFastTargetAddressInputCount + c_arg_count + extra_input_count);
273
274 ExternalReference::Type ref_type = ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL;
275
276 // The inputs to {Call} node for the fast call look like:
277 // [fast callee, receiver, ... C arguments, [optional Options], effect,
278 // control].
279 //
280 // The first input node represents the target address for the fast call.
281 // If the function is not overloaded (c_functions.size() == 1) this is the
282 // address associated to the first and only element in the c_functions vector.
283 // If there are multiple overloads the value of this input will be set later
284 // with a Phi node created by AdaptOverloadedFastCallArgument.
285 inputs[kFastTargetAddressInputIndex] =
286 (c_functions.size() == 1) ? __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(
287 c_functions[0].address, ref_type))
288 : nullptr;
289
290 for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count; ++i) {
291 inputs[i + kFastTargetAddressInputCount] =
292 get_parameter_(i, overloads_resolution_result, &if_error);
293 if (overloads_resolution_result.target_address) {
294 inputs[kFastTargetAddressInputIndex] =
295 overloads_resolution_result.target_address;
296 }
297 }
298 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(inputs[kFastTargetAddressInputIndex]);
299
300 MachineSignature::Builder builder(
301 graph()->zone(), 1, c_arg_count + (c_signature->HasOptions() ? 1 : 0));
302 MachineType return_type =
303 MachineType::TypeForCType(c_signature->ReturnInfo());
304 builder.AddReturn(return_type);
305 for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count; ++i) {
306 CTypeInfo type = c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i);
307 MachineType machine_type =
308 type.GetSequenceType() == CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kScalar
309 ? MachineType::TypeForCType(type)
310 : MachineType::AnyTagged();
311 builder.AddParam(machine_type);
312 }
313
314 Node* stack_slot = nullptr;
315 if (c_signature->HasOptions()) {
316 const int kAlign = alignof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions);
317 const int kSize = sizeof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions);
318 // If this check fails, you've probably added new fields to
319 // v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, which means you'll need to write code
320 // that initializes and reads from them too.
321 static_assert(kSize == sizeof(uintptr_t) * 3);
322 stack_slot = __ StackSlot(kSize, kAlign);
323
324 __ Store(
325 StoreRepresentation(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, kNoWriteBarrier),
326 stack_slot,
327 static_cast<int>(offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, fallback)),
328 __ Int32Constant(0));
329
330 Node* data_argument_to_pass = __ AdaptLocalArgument(data_argument);
331
332 __ Store(StoreRepresentation(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
333 kNoWriteBarrier),
334 stack_slot,
335 static_cast<int>(offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, data)),
336 data_argument_to_pass);
337
338 initialize_options_(stack_slot);
339
340 builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer()); // stack_slot
341 }
342
343 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
344 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(graph()->zone(), builder.Build());
345
346 Node* c_call_result =
347 WrapFastCall(call_descriptor, c_arg_count + extra_input_count + 1, inputs,
348 inputs[0], c_signature, c_arg_count, stack_slot);
349
350 Node* fast_call_result = convert_return_value_(c_signature, c_call_result);
351
352 auto merge = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
353 if (c_signature->HasOptions()) {
354 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(stack_slot);
355 Node* load = __ Load(
356 MachineType::Int32(), stack_slot,
357 static_cast<int>(offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, fallback)));
358
359 Node* is_zero = __ Word32Equal(load, __ Int32Constant(0));
360 __ Branch(is_zero, &if_success, &if_error);
361 } else {
362 __ Goto(&if_success);
363 }
364
365 // We need to generate a fallback (both fast and slow call) in case:
366 // 1) the generated code might fail, in case e.g. a Smi was passed where
367 // a JSObject was expected and an error must be thrown or
368 // 2) the embedder requested fallback possibility via providing options arg.
369 // None of the above usually holds true for Wasm functions with primitive
370 // types only, so we avoid generating an extra branch here.
371 DCHECK_IMPLIES(c_signature->HasOptions(), if_error.IsUsed());
372 if (if_error.IsUsed()) {
373 // Generate direct slow call.
374 __ Bind(&if_error);
375 {
376 Node* slow_call_result = generate_slow_api_call_();
377 __ Goto(&merge, slow_call_result);
378 }
379 }
380
381 __ Bind(&if_success);
382 __ Goto(&merge, fast_call_result);
383
384 __ Bind(&merge);
385 return merge.PhiAt(0);
386}
387
388#undef __
389
390Node* BuildFastApiCall(Isolate* isolate, Graph* graph,
391 GraphAssembler* graph_assembler,
392 const FastApiCallFunctionVector& c_functions,
393 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature, Node* data_argument,
394 const GetParameter& get_parameter,
395 const ConvertReturnValue& convert_return_value,
396 const InitializeOptions& initialize_options,
397 const GenerateSlowApiCall& generate_slow_api_call) {
398 FastApiCallBuilder builder(isolate, graph, graph_assembler, get_parameter,
399 convert_return_value, initialize_options,
400 generate_slow_api_call);
401 return builder.Build(c_functions, c_signature, data_argument);
402}
